Maloney's is a good place to grab a quick bite for lunch or even before a lightning game if you want to avoid the huge crowd at Fergs. I work in the area and have relied on this establishment for last minute lunches when I am too lazy to pack my lunch at home. Their shepherds pie is a go to staple for me, it is really good and you get a good portion. I have tried their fish and chips and they were not bad but I am just not a fan of fried foods. When I want to eat something healthier they have a good fish and veggies option. You can get the a steamed or blacked piece of chicken breast or whatever fish fillet options they have with a side of steamed veggies for under $10. I will typically ask that they include fresh lemon with my fish as it just makes the blackened fish taste so much better.  The ambience is very chill. The inside is a bit dark and they have arcade games as well. They do have an enclosed patio and part of the inside bar extends outside. The girls working the bar are always friendly and pretty attentive.  I would not say the food is out of this world but it is not bad; this is a chain after all. If you want a quick lunch and happen to be in the area I would recommend it.
